  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nI'm trying to run the Docker latest unstable using the Local Testnet scripts, but doesn't contain Lighthouse binaries: \r\n\r\n`lcli: command not found`\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\nBuilding from Docker [latest unstable image](https://hub.docker.com/layers/sigp/lighthouse/latest-unstable/images/sha256-a4c2e9ff5e06fdf6e7ebed86bf7545e27cf24edbba9ab10d9c9ea49f90d5e1f5).\r\n\r\n## Present Behaviour\r\n\r\nWhen starting the Docker image and running the Local testnet scripts inside the container, this message is shown:\r\n\r\n```\r\n12:53:43.705 [main] INFO  üê≥ [sigp/lighthouse:latest] - Creating container for image: sigp/lighthouse:latest\r\n12:53:46.269 [main] INFO  üê≥ [sigp/lighthouse:latest] - Starting container with ID: c4b7badac4e3133b4b393e41fd9140352cf806ab40c67fd6e1713dc1f25386ed\r\n12:53:46.663 [main] INFO  üê≥ [sigp/lighthouse:latest] - Container sigp/lighthouse:latest is starting: c4b7badac4e3133b4b393e41fd9140352cf806ab40c67fd6e1713dc1f25386ed\r\nSpecification generated at /root/.lighthouse/local-testnet/testnet.\r\nGenerating 1024 validators concurrently... (this may take a while)\r\n./setup.sh: line 11: lcli: command not found\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\n\r\nIn the previous versions, the command `lcli` was available inside the Docker container.\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\nRun the Docker image mapping the Local testnet scripts to the root directory. Then run `start.sh` inside the container.\r\n",
